{"amendments":[{"body":"Prevent duplicate completion journal events on terminal replays that backfill optional metadata. `update_task_run` explicitly supports replaying an already-finalized row and backfilling missing `plan_hash`/`outcome_detail` (`src/adapters/fs.rs:2425-2457`, `src/adapters/fs.rs:2798-2828`), but the completion event payload includes those optional fields (`src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:233-245`) and `append_event_if_missing` only deduplicates exact `details` matches (`src/adapters/fs.rs:2326-2341`). If the first completion write succeeded without `plan_hash`/`outcome_detail` and a later replay adds them, the same attempt gets a second `BeadCompleted`/`BeadFailed` journal entry instead of repairing the original event.","rationale":"This breaks the idempotency guarantee documented in `update_task_run` and produces duplicate completion history for a single attempt whenever missing metadata is filled in later."},{"body":"Preserve `Paused` during lineage reconciliation instead of forcing it back to `Ready`. `reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage` unconditionally rewrites any non-terminal milestone with no active bead and any prior task runs to `Ready` (`src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:213-216`), and `update_task_run` persists that reconciled snapshot on every completion/backfill (`src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:574-583`). Because `Paused` is a first-class lifecycle state (`src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs:58-59`), replaying lineage on a paused milestone silently clears the operator-imposed pause.","rationale":"This is a workflow regression: a pause can be lost just by repairing run metadata, which can let execution resume without an explicit lifecycle transition."}],"summary":"Reviewed the milestone lineage changes across `src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs`, `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs`, and `src/adapters/fs.rs`, and ran `cargo test milestone_record` successfully. I found two correctness issues: completion replays can duplicate journal events when they enrich optional metadata, and lineage reconciliation currently clears `paused` milestones back to `ready` during update/backfill flows."}